1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:06,001
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:00:08,515 --> 00:00:10,785
(Lee Na Young)

3
00:00:16,755 --> 00:00:19,395
(Jung Eun Chae)

4
00:00:21,035 --> 00:00:23,665
(Lee Chung Ah)

5
00:00:31,545 --> 00:00:35,145
(Honour)

6
00:00:35,715 --> 00:00:38,555
(Supported by the Culture Ministry
and Korea's Creative Content Agency)

7
00:00:39,285 --> 00:00:40,791
(All people, incidents, and backgrounds...)

8
00:00:40,815 --> 00:00:41,831
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

9
00:00:41,855 --> 00:00:43,131
(Also, children and animals were
filmed under production guidelines.)

10
00:00:43,155 --> 00:00:48,055
(From an old friend, Park Ju Hwan)

11
00:00:52,495 --> 00:00:53,495
It's been a while.

12
00:00:54,195 --> 00:00:55,565
I missed you, Ra Young.

13
00:01:07,915 --> 00:01:12,385
What's with that look? It's
like you've seen a ghost.

14
00:01:18,225 --> 00:01:21,055
I heard the news. About
your tenth anniversary.

15
00:01:21,125 --> 00:01:23,645
So I stopped by to congratulate
you, even if I'm a little late.

16
00:01:24,625 --> 00:01:25,985
(From an old friend, Park Ju Hwan)

17
00:01:28,335 --> 00:01:31,135
Where are Shin Jae and
Hyun Jin? Are they inside?

18
00:01:33,875 --> 00:01:35,305
They're not here right now.

19
00:01:36,905 --> 00:01:37,905
Really?

20
00:01:38,505 --> 00:01:41,145
That's a shame. I hoped to
see them while I was here.

21
00:01:43,215 --> 00:01:45,545
Let's go out. We can grab a coffee.

22
00:01:50,255 --> 00:01:52,001
(Hankuk University
College of Law Newsletter)

23
00:01:52,025 --> 00:01:53,185
By any chance,

24
00:01:53,455 --> 00:01:55,701
what about the male
student that went missing?

25
00:01:55,725 --> 00:01:57,195
Was his body ever found?

26
00:01:57,265 --> 00:01:58,325
You mean Ju Hwan?

27
00:01:59,165 --> 00:02:00,665
Ju Hwan didn't die.

28
00:02:01,065 --> 00:02:02,825
He was found in a
hospital a few days later.

29
00:02:03,165 --> 00:02:05,705
A passerby found him
and took him to the hospital,

30
00:02:06,265 --> 00:02:07,935
but I guess they couldn't identify him.

31
00:02:09,675 --> 00:02:13,075
If he's alive, why couldn't
they find the culprit?

32
00:02:13,275 --> 00:02:15,275
Because Ju Hwan lost his memory.

33
00:02:15,575 --> 00:02:18,985
Due to a cerebral haemorrhage,
he lost all memory of the accident.

34
00:02:19,515 --> 00:02:23,115
I hear the after-effects were
severe. He took leave for rehab,

35
00:02:23,185 --> 00:02:27,395
and went abroad. I haven't
heard from him since then.

36
00:02:28,795 --> 00:02:30,525
Park Ju Hwan.

37
00:02:33,195 --> 00:02:34,595
Spyware?

38
00:02:34,765 --> 00:02:38,535
The Connect In app. They
were hacking our phones.

39
00:02:38,735 --> 00:02:41,735
- They were watching our every move.
- That's insane.

40
00:02:42,235 --> 00:02:44,105
Wait, how did they even know it was us?

41
00:02:46,175 --> 00:02:48,945
They could've just been
collecting data from all users.

42
00:02:49,315 --> 00:02:50,315
(Trainer)

43
00:02:51,815 --> 00:02:54,415
Or we might have gotten flagged
by one of their security filters.

44
00:02:54,955 --> 00:02:56,685
(Voice detected does not match VIP 0911.)

45
00:02:56,755 --> 00:02:58,085
Or it could be both.

46
00:02:59,585 --> 00:03:02,155
Gosh, I can't believe the
lengths these guys go to.

47
00:03:02,225 --> 00:03:05,225
You need AI technology to do
this kind of real-time monitoring.

48
00:03:05,325 --> 00:03:07,865
But to run an AI with this
level of deep learning...

49
00:03:08,265 --> 00:03:09,871
This is no normal trafficking ring.

50
00:03:09,895 --> 00:03:11,565
It's not amateurs who slapped an app,

51
00:03:11,635 --> 00:03:14,675
and a website together, running
it as a gambling operation.

52
00:03:14,875 --> 00:03:16,575
These guys are total pros.

53
00:03:21,115 --> 00:03:22,645
Where's Attorney Yoon?

54
00:03:22,845 --> 00:03:27,115
She stepped out to meet a friend.
The one who sent the flowers...

55
00:03:27,385 --> 00:03:29,715
A friend? Who?

56
00:03:32,325 --> 00:03:33,895
(From an old friend, Park Ju Hwan)

57
00:03:36,795 --> 00:03:38,525
Which way did Attorney Yoon go?

58
00:03:47,535 --> 00:03:48,675
So when did you get back

59
00:03:50,205 --> 00:03:53,645
- to Korea?
- That's ancient history.

60
00:03:54,115 --> 00:03:56,975
I was at a provincial office. I
just moved to Seoul recently.

61
00:03:59,285 --> 00:04:00,555
I thought I'd say hello,

62
00:04:02,385 --> 00:04:03,745
so I just dropped by for a minute.

63
00:04:06,255 --> 00:04:07,971
(Park Je Yeol, Seoul Mujin
Regional Prosecutors' Office)

64
00:04:07,995 --> 00:04:10,095
You changed your name?

65
00:04:10,155 --> 00:04:11,841
You know how it is.

66
00:04:11,865 --> 00:04:14,465
Victims often change their
names after an accident.

67
00:04:14,795 --> 00:04:17,205
Because they want to put it behind them.

68
00:04:17,705 --> 00:04:19,465
I guess that's why I became a prosecutor.

69
00:04:19,905 --> 00:04:24,345
Because I know all too well
that until the culprit is caught,

70
00:04:25,245 --> 00:04:27,615
the victim can never escape
their own personal hell.

71
00:04:29,245 --> 00:04:31,745
A victim?

72
00:04:31,815 --> 00:04:35,055
My head was crushed in. I
wasn't the perpetrator, was I?

73
00:04:43,225 --> 00:04:44,625
I'm sorry about what happened.

74
00:04:44,925 --> 00:04:49,035
That they never caught the culprit,
and that you lost your memory.

75
00:05:00,745 --> 00:05:04,045
Considering you were so sorry,
you had no problem dumping me.

76
00:05:04,715 --> 00:05:07,685
You never even visited me
in the hospital once after that.

77
00:05:07,915 --> 00:05:11,555
And on top of all that, you
broke up with me over a text.

78
00:05:11,725 --> 00:05:14,895
Can you imagine how hurt I was?

79
00:05:15,395 --> 00:05:17,465
But I get it.

80
00:05:19,865 --> 00:05:21,625
Complications from a
cerebral haemorrhage.

81
00:05:22,265 --> 00:05:24,835
I'm still suffering from them.

82
00:05:25,305 --> 00:05:29,975
I guess you were just too
pretty to stick by a sick boyfriend.

83
00:05:30,235 --> 00:05:31,245
But of course,

84
00:05:33,175 --> 00:05:34,575
you still are

85
00:05:36,475 --> 00:05:37,645
just as beautiful.

86
00:05:41,855 --> 00:05:44,625
And look what we have
here. Another welcome face.

87
00:05:53,565 --> 00:05:55,965
How could I ignore a
friend I've missed so dearly?

88
00:05:56,265 --> 00:05:57,465
That wouldn't be right.

89
00:05:58,765 --> 00:06:00,065
It's hot.

90
00:06:04,605 --> 00:06:05,805
It's been a while.

91
00:06:06,075 --> 00:06:09,375
It has. What's it been, 20 years?

92
00:06:09,415 --> 00:06:12,115
I heard you moved abroad, so
I didn't think I'd see you again.

93
00:06:12,445 --> 00:06:15,055
But I guess life is full of surprises.

94
00:06:17,115 --> 00:06:19,985
Why's that? Was there a reason

95
00:06:20,325 --> 00:06:25,095
- you didn't want to see me again?
- Because I've always hated you.

96
00:06:25,665 --> 00:06:29,465
I was against it from the start,
when Ra Young started dating you.

97
00:06:37,305 --> 00:06:39,351
(Park Je Yeol, Seoul Mujin
Regional Prosecutors' Office)

98
00:06:39,375 --> 00:06:41,115
Goodness, you became a prosecutor?

99
00:06:41,975 --> 00:06:43,615
And you changed your name.

100
00:06:44,345 --> 00:06:48,415
What, did you commit a crime?
That's usually what ex-cons do.

101
00:06:48,655 --> 00:06:51,585
- Your name's still the same.
- That's because.

102
00:06:52,325 --> 00:06:54,455
I have nothing to be ashamed of.

103
00:06:54,925 --> 00:06:58,495
That's a relief. I'd hate to
see a friend as a suspect.

104
00:07:00,225 --> 00:07:01,735
Let's wrap up this little reunion.

105
00:07:02,135 --> 00:07:05,705
- We'll be seeing each other again.
- We will?

106
00:07:06,605 --> 00:07:09,405
I'm planning to reinvestigate
what happened back then.

107
00:07:10,105 --> 00:07:13,875
And since it happened so long
ago, I might need all of your help.

108
00:07:15,745 --> 00:07:16,775
See you around.

109
00:07:29,955 --> 00:07:31,065
Ra Young.

110
00:07:31,895 --> 00:07:33,025
Ra Young.

111
00:07:38,465 --> 00:07:39,565
Ra Young.

112
00:07:41,175 --> 00:07:42,275
Ra Young.

113
00:07:47,005 --> 00:07:48,815
Yoon Ra Young!

114
00:07:49,715 --> 00:07:52,185
Look at me.

115
00:07:53,785 --> 00:07:54,815
It's okay.

116
00:07:55,715 --> 00:07:57,085
Okay, breathe.

117
00:07:57,585 --> 00:07:58,685
Again.

118
00:08:02,055 --> 00:08:03,125
Good.

119
00:08:04,195 --> 00:08:05,195
One more time.

120
00:08:07,795 --> 00:08:08,995
Good.

121
00:08:10,595 --> 00:08:14,075
That jerk. How dare he come here?

122
00:08:19,145 --> 00:08:21,225
(Found the Connect In app.
(Call me before you come.)

123
00:08:23,245 --> 00:08:26,445
Is the pain that bad? Should
I ask for more painkillers?

124
00:08:29,285 --> 00:08:30,585
It's Brahms.

125
00:08:31,955 --> 00:08:33,955
Brahms and Dvorak.

126
00:08:34,255 --> 00:08:37,595
Mahler, Bruckner, Shostakovich.

127
00:08:38,365 --> 00:08:42,695
In painting, Baroque.
Caravaggio, Rubens, and van Dyck.

128
00:08:43,065 --> 00:08:46,505
I've read everything by
Stendhal and Flaubert.

129
00:08:46,705 --> 00:08:50,805
And I loved John Steinbeck,
Emile Zola, and Victor Hugo.

130
00:08:51,345 --> 00:08:55,345
For wine, Burgundy. On special
occasions, Domaine Leroy.

131
00:08:55,645 --> 00:08:58,145
For whiskey, a Speyside single malt.

132
00:08:59,085 --> 00:09:00,385
You have excellent taste.

133
00:09:01,185 --> 00:09:02,915
You taught me everything.

134
00:09:03,415 --> 00:09:05,355
Everything I love.

135
00:09:07,155 --> 00:09:10,555
If I take away everything
I learned from you,

136
00:09:11,695 --> 00:09:13,465
what would even be left of me?

137
00:09:18,135 --> 00:09:20,205
I found the Connect In app.

138
00:09:20,735 --> 00:09:22,135
On your phone.

139
00:09:40,185 --> 00:09:42,225
Don't tell me you're going to deny it.

140
00:09:44,865 --> 00:09:46,195
I'm not sure.

141
00:09:46,795 --> 00:09:49,995
I'm afraid I don't know
what you're talking about.

142
00:09:51,405 --> 00:09:54,105
I also found proof. On your phone.

143
00:09:54,175 --> 00:09:57,605
And what exactly is this
"proof" you're talking about?

144
00:09:57,975 --> 00:09:59,105
Why don't you check again?

145
00:10:01,315 --> 00:10:03,845
You seem to have caused this scene over it,

146
00:10:04,145 --> 00:10:05,345
but that's a shame.

147
00:10:05,915 --> 00:10:07,045
And another thing.

148
00:10:07,585 --> 00:10:10,115
Even if what you're claiming is true,

149
00:10:10,985 --> 00:10:12,685
what's the big deal?

150
00:10:13,555 --> 00:10:14,555
What did you just say?

151
00:10:14,855 --> 00:10:18,495
You need to grow up, Shin Jae.
Before you leap without looking,

152
00:10:18,565 --> 00:10:20,425
you need to weigh the consequences.

153
00:10:22,295 --> 00:10:24,435
What you stand to gain from this,

154
00:10:25,305 --> 00:10:26,735
and what you stand to lose.

155
00:10:28,305 --> 00:10:32,175
I can't believe what I'm
hearing. Was that a threat?

156
00:10:34,145 --> 00:10:36,745
Either way, you only have one choice.

157
00:10:37,485 --> 00:10:39,145
Join me, or

158
00:10:39,585 --> 00:10:42,115
spend the rest of your life being
pushed around by your mother.

159
00:10:43,385 --> 00:10:46,855
Think it over if you
want to protect I and J.

160
00:10:47,355 --> 00:10:49,425
There's no point in
discussing this further.

161
00:10:50,295 --> 00:10:51,495
Leave.

162
00:11:04,375 --> 00:11:06,305
How could you do this?

163
00:11:07,675 --> 00:11:09,875
I should be asking you the same thing.

164
00:11:10,275 --> 00:11:12,045
Did I teach you to be like this?

165
00:11:12,445 --> 00:11:14,855
To invade someone's privacy like this?

166
00:11:41,045 --> 00:11:43,191
What's going on? Why is the app gone?

167
00:11:43,215 --> 00:11:46,745
We'll talk about that later.
A bombshell just dropped.

168
00:11:48,215 --> 00:11:49,285
Park Ju Hwan.

169
00:11:49,685 --> 00:11:52,455
What are you talking about? Park Ju Hwan?

170
00:11:52,625 --> 00:11:56,995
He came to the office. And get
this. That jerk is a prosecutor now.

171
00:11:57,695 --> 00:11:58,895
How's Ra Young?

172
00:12:09,535 --> 00:12:12,245
I'm fine. I'm not in my 20s anymore.

173
00:12:13,045 --> 00:12:15,775
I tell our clients that
everything will be okay,

174
00:12:15,875 --> 00:12:17,615
so I can't afford to fall apart, can I?

175
00:12:21,315 --> 00:12:24,115
I'm going to eat something spicy.
Something mind-numbingly spicy.

176
00:12:24,255 --> 00:12:25,785
That's what we need today.

177
00:12:40,865 --> 00:12:42,975
All right, let's hurry. I'm starving.

178
00:12:43,475 --> 00:12:45,175
So what do you need us to do?

179
00:12:55,455 --> 00:12:57,155
When did he get back to Korea?

180
00:12:57,555 --> 00:12:58,985
Seems like a while ago.

181
00:13:00,425 --> 00:13:02,555
We should've kept better tabs on him.

182
00:13:02,825 --> 00:13:04,625
Before he could just pop up like this.

183
00:13:04,965 --> 00:13:08,365
How were we to know he'd changed his name?

184
00:13:09,365 --> 00:13:10,765
So how did he seem?

185
00:13:11,105 --> 00:13:13,185
Did it look like he's really
gotten his memory back?

186
00:13:13,535 --> 00:13:14,775
It's hard to say.

187
00:13:15,435 --> 00:13:18,981
I'm not sure he's testing the
waters, saying he'll reinvestigate,

188
00:13:19,005 --> 00:13:20,165
or if he remembers something.

189
00:13:25,985 --> 00:13:29,855
I almost hope he hasn't
gotten his memory back.

190
00:13:30,755 --> 00:13:34,395
If he's acting that brazen
knowing what he did to me,

191
00:13:35,025 --> 00:13:36,025
it's just too

192
00:13:37,425 --> 00:13:38,595
agonizing for me.

193
00:13:39,565 --> 00:13:40,925
I could never forgive him.

194
00:13:57,945 --> 00:13:59,015
Attorney Yoon?

195
00:14:02,915 --> 00:14:03,985
Min Seo.

196
00:14:05,255 --> 00:14:06,855
Something I ate isn't sitting right.

197
00:14:07,555 --> 00:14:08,625
I'm okay.

198
00:14:09,655 --> 00:14:11,495
Don't worry about me. You get some rest.

199
00:14:24,745 --> 00:14:29,575
(Mujin Police Station)

200
00:14:34,515 --> 00:14:38,085
- Hey, sunshine. Chief wants you.
- Right.

201
00:14:41,895 --> 00:14:44,055
- Seung Jin.
- Yes?

202
00:14:44,995 --> 00:14:47,835
Do you recognise this person?

203
00:14:50,295 --> 00:14:53,935
Hey, he looks really familiar. What?

204
00:14:55,035 --> 00:14:56,735
Isn't this Prosecutor Park Je Yeol?

205
00:14:56,835 --> 00:14:59,205
Right? It's him, isn't it?

206
00:14:59,375 --> 00:15:01,375
Yes, I think you're right.

207
00:15:01,715 --> 00:15:03,615
Looks like he was a classmate of your wife.

208
00:15:04,115 --> 00:15:07,645
Then again, the cream of
the crop all stick together.

209
00:15:11,155 --> 00:15:12,625
Why would he change his name?

210
00:15:13,555 --> 00:15:17,095
Hey, you'd better get to the
Chief. He'll flip out if you're late.

211
00:15:17,395 --> 00:15:18,995
- All right. I'll be right back.
- Okay.

212
00:15:19,765 --> 00:15:21,335
- You wanted to see me, sir?
- Yes.

213
00:15:21,365 --> 00:15:22,595
(Seoul Mujin Police Station)

214
00:15:22,735 --> 00:15:24,495
How many cases are
you working on right now?

215
00:15:24,935 --> 00:15:26,435
The Samyang-dong serial theft case...

216
00:15:26,505 --> 00:15:28,905
You can handle one more file then, right?

217
00:15:31,745 --> 00:15:34,945
It's a 20-year-old case. I
need you to handle it with care.

218
00:15:35,475 --> 00:15:37,785
The victim is a sitting prosecutor.

219
00:15:42,085 --> 00:15:43,485
(Witness statement)

220
00:15:45,085 --> 00:15:46,231
(2005 Hankuk University
student murder attempt)

221
00:15:46,255 --> 00:15:47,325
Is the victim...

222
00:15:48,395 --> 00:15:51,395
- Prosecutor Park Je Yeol?
- Yes, he is.

223
00:15:52,225 --> 00:15:55,065
He specifically asked for you.
Do you two know each other?

224
00:15:56,935 --> 00:15:58,815
(2005 Hankuk University
student murder attempt)

225
00:15:59,635 --> 00:16:01,875
(Park Je Yeol, Seoul Mujin
Regional Prosecutors' Office)

226
00:16:03,935 --> 00:16:05,205
Doesn't something seem off?

227
00:16:05,305 --> 00:16:08,315
So that jerk Park Ju Hwan was
the prosecutor on Yoo Jeong's case?

228
00:16:08,375 --> 00:16:10,575
And on top of that, he had
the case reassigned to him.

229
00:16:10,815 --> 00:16:14,185
- So he took her case on purpose?
- Most likely.

230
00:16:14,685 --> 00:16:16,855
But you know what's even stranger?

231
00:16:17,755 --> 00:16:20,825
Park Ju Hwan had met
Jo Yoo Jeong a year ago.

232
00:16:20,885 --> 00:16:22,725
She was a suspect in
an aggravated theft case.

233
00:16:22,825 --> 00:16:24,125
You think this is a coincidence?

234
00:16:24,195 --> 00:16:27,295
There's one way to find out.
I'll go meet Yoo Jeong's sister.

235
00:16:30,335 --> 00:16:32,905
Yoo Jeong wasn't
actually trying to steal it.

236
00:16:33,505 --> 00:16:35,305
At the shop where she worked part-time,

237
00:16:35,705 --> 00:16:37,905
she accidentally spilled a
drink on a customer's bag.

238
00:16:38,305 --> 00:16:40,045
She must have panicked.

239
00:16:40,305 --> 00:16:44,815
So she and a friend from work
took the bag to try and clean it.

240
00:16:44,885 --> 00:16:46,605
But they ended up getting accused of theft.

241
00:16:47,345 --> 00:16:50,355
The customer refused to
settle, so we were really worried,

242
00:16:50,515 --> 00:16:53,685
but luckily, the prosecutor
decided to suspend the indictment.

243
00:16:53,955 --> 00:16:56,395
For aggravated theft, with no settlement,

244
00:16:56,695 --> 00:16:58,015
he just suspended the indictment?

245
00:17:01,265 --> 00:17:02,595
Min Seo, have you, by any chance,

246
00:17:02,935 --> 00:17:05,235
ever met a prosecutor named Park Je Yeol?

247
00:17:05,405 --> 00:17:07,435
No, I've never met him.

248
00:17:08,435 --> 00:17:12,605
Min Seo, how did you end
up working for Connect?

249
00:17:12,945 --> 00:17:14,205
You know Lee Seon Hwa, right?

250
00:17:14,775 --> 00:17:17,445
- It was because of her.
- Lee Seon Hwa?

251
00:17:17,945 --> 00:17:20,385
She took out a loan in my name,

252
00:17:20,445 --> 00:17:22,555
and she said part of it
was transferred to them.

253
00:17:22,685 --> 00:17:25,685
I was told I had to work
at Connect to pay it off.

254
00:17:33,725 --> 00:17:35,195
(Case report)

255
00:17:35,265 --> 00:17:36,265
(Habitual drug use)

256
00:17:46,375 --> 00:17:49,045
- Hey, where's Lee Seon Hwa?
- Seon Hwa? She skipped town.

257
00:17:49,445 --> 00:17:50,675
You have no idea where?

258
00:17:50,745 --> 00:17:53,615
Kidding? If I knew, I'd have gone
after her. She ripped me off too.

259
00:17:53,785 --> 00:17:56,985
That witch would squeeze
blood from a stone.

260
00:17:58,555 --> 00:18:01,595
This is her stuff. I was hoping
I'd find something valuable,

261
00:18:01,655 --> 00:18:03,655
but it's all just junk. Gosh.

262
00:18:09,895 --> 00:18:11,435
It's a trial summons.

263
00:18:11,505 --> 00:18:15,581
That's probably why she ran. She
got her indictment suspended last time,

264
00:18:15,605 --> 00:18:17,811
- but she must've been caught again.
- A suspended indictment?

265
00:18:17,835 --> 00:18:21,075
Yes, that junkie. She'll
actually do time for this, right?

266
00:18:21,145 --> 00:18:22,275
It's her fourth offence now.

267
00:18:22,615 --> 00:18:24,685
- Darn! My money.
- Wait.

268
00:18:25,085 --> 00:18:26,715
She was a three-time offender,

269
00:18:26,785 --> 00:18:28,391
and she still got a suspended indictment?

270
00:18:28,415 --> 00:18:31,255
You said you'd kill them
next time, so that's a threat.

271
00:18:31,985 --> 00:18:34,925
And since you were holding a
stick with nails in it, it's "aggravated."

272
00:18:38,425 --> 00:18:40,725
While you're serving seven
years for aggravated threats,

273
00:18:41,365 --> 00:18:43,925
have you decided which orphanage
to send your little brother to?

274
00:18:44,935 --> 00:18:49,005
I did it because I was so angry
they bullied my little brother.

275
00:18:50,535 --> 00:18:54,675
Sir, please let me off
the hook just this once.

276
00:18:57,445 --> 00:18:59,185
Let you off the hook?

277
00:19:02,585 --> 00:19:03,715
Shall I?

278
00:19:05,125 --> 00:19:06,325
You really want me to do that?

279
00:19:06,955 --> 00:19:09,025
Yes, please.

280
00:19:12,865 --> 00:19:14,065
All right, then. Maybe I will.

281
00:19:14,795 --> 00:19:15,795
Really?

282
00:19:16,335 --> 00:19:17,965
That's up to you.

283
00:19:20,635 --> 00:19:22,181
(Jo Yoo Jeong, Prosecutor
Park Je Yeol, Lee Seon Hwa)

284
00:19:22,205 --> 00:19:23,635
Check this out.

285
00:19:28,045 --> 00:19:30,375
Both women, after being
handled by Park Ju Hwan...

286
00:19:31,115 --> 00:19:32,185
No.

287
00:19:32,685 --> 00:19:36,185
Through Prosecutor Park Je Yeol,
they received suspended indictments,

288
00:19:36,315 --> 00:19:38,025
and were then exploited by Connect.

289
00:19:38,685 --> 00:19:40,845
In Lee Seon Hwa's case,
Min Seo had to take her place.

290
00:19:41,425 --> 00:19:43,955
It's clear that some of the victims

291
00:19:44,025 --> 00:19:46,095
were likely supplied to the app

292
00:19:46,165 --> 00:19:47,165
through Park Je Yeol.

293
00:19:47,225 --> 00:19:48,825
By using his authority to indict people.

294
00:19:50,635 --> 00:19:52,965
So Park Je Yeol is part of Connect?

295
00:19:57,435 --> 00:19:59,445
Even a prosecutor is
part of this whole scheme?

296
00:19:59,745 --> 00:20:02,475
If that's true, then all
the pieces fall into place.

297
00:20:03,215 --> 00:20:05,815
Including who's been using
our pasts to attack us all this time.

298
00:20:06,145 --> 00:20:08,185
But right now, the only evidence we have

299
00:20:08,515 --> 00:20:09,955
is all circumstantial.

300
00:20:11,015 --> 00:20:13,585
If only that darn app
hadn't been taken down...

301
00:20:15,855 --> 00:20:16,955
So, have you decided?

302
00:20:17,795 --> 00:20:19,725
What you're going to
do about Attorney Kwon?

303
00:20:21,635 --> 00:20:23,435
What's there to decide?

304
00:20:24,165 --> 00:20:26,835
Now that I know who's behind this darn app.

305
00:20:28,335 --> 00:20:29,851
(Jo Yoo Jeong, Prosecutor
Park Je Yeol, Lee Seon Hwa)

306
00:20:29,875 --> 00:20:31,151
(Aggravated theft,
suspension of indictment?)

307
00:20:31,175 --> 00:20:32,655
(Drug use, suspension of indictment?)

308
00:20:44,185 --> 00:20:46,725
This just arrived by courier.
It's from Attorney Kang Shin Jae.

309
00:20:52,725 --> 00:20:55,205
(The laws in the Republic of
Korea don't call what you did...)

310
00:20:57,295 --> 00:20:58,605
(Managing Partner Kang Shin Jae)

311
00:20:59,005 --> 00:21:01,405
The laws in the Republic of
Korea don't call what you did

312
00:21:01,435 --> 00:21:03,505
a matter of privacy. They call it a crime.

313
00:21:04,535 --> 00:21:08,245
When the wind blows, I will sway.
And yet, the flowers still bloom.

314
00:21:12,885 --> 00:21:16,685
All the attorneys who resigned
are waiting at the meeting place.

315
00:21:17,055 --> 00:21:18,185
What are your orders?

316
00:21:19,325 --> 00:21:20,685
If they've come to a consensus,

317
00:21:21,895 --> 00:21:23,155
then we must pave the way.

318
00:21:24,425 --> 00:21:25,565
Let's go.

319
00:21:31,805 --> 00:21:33,035
Welcome.

320
00:21:34,805 --> 00:21:36,005
Mind if I join you?

321
00:21:42,375 --> 00:21:45,345
- It's been a while.
- I heard you came looking for me,

322
00:21:45,645 --> 00:21:47,325
so I thought we should at least say hello.

323
00:21:48,955 --> 00:21:50,355
How did you find me here?

324
00:21:50,685 --> 00:21:54,625
Around here, if I put my mind to
it, there isn't much I can't find out.

325
00:21:55,495 --> 00:21:56,595
You're looking good.

326
00:21:59,495 --> 00:22:00,495
I'm great.

327
00:22:01,025 --> 00:22:04,465
I endure the searing pain in
my right arm several times a day,

328
00:22:04,835 --> 00:22:08,335
and I have to choke down a
fistful of painkillers every day,

329
00:22:09,405 --> 00:22:10,505
but I'm doing just great.

330
00:22:11,335 --> 00:22:12,345
So,

331
00:22:12,645 --> 00:22:14,345
are you trying to get your revenge now?

332
00:22:15,015 --> 00:22:18,785
Why? You're only scared now?

333
00:22:21,345 --> 00:22:23,915
- So you've regained your memory.
- Is that all?

334
00:22:24,585 --> 00:22:26,025
I also got my hands on the evidence.

335
00:22:37,565 --> 00:22:39,535
The DNA sample you
guys tried to sneak out...

336
00:22:40,465 --> 00:22:44,735
It just so happens to match the
suspect's DNA from the scene.

337
00:22:49,315 --> 00:22:50,945
Then I guess you also remember

338
00:22:51,475 --> 00:22:54,915
what you did to Ra Young that night.

339
00:22:58,255 --> 00:23:01,595
What difference does
that make now, Shin Jae?

340
00:23:01,725 --> 00:23:03,595
It's not like you can prove it, anyway.

341
00:23:04,055 --> 00:23:06,625
- What?
- Yoon Ra Young and I were dating.

342
00:23:07,165 --> 00:23:10,035
We were just in love,
like any other couple.

343
00:23:11,635 --> 00:23:13,665
People really can't stand you guys.

344
00:23:14,005 --> 00:23:15,975
They say you're shrill and exhausting.

345
00:23:16,375 --> 00:23:18,905
If I just add a little fuel to that fire,

346
00:23:19,275 --> 00:23:22,575
who do you think will get
burned? Me, or you guys?

347
00:23:25,085 --> 00:23:26,185
What do you want?

348
00:23:26,785 --> 00:23:29,155
Back off from Connect.

349
00:23:30,585 --> 00:23:32,055
And if I won't?

350
00:23:35,755 --> 00:23:37,495
Are you really prepared to be broken?

351
00:23:39,765 --> 00:23:40,925
I can be.

352
00:23:42,735 --> 00:23:45,535
The one who'll be hurt
the most by this fight

353
00:23:47,165 --> 00:23:48,405
will be Yoon Ra Young.

354
00:24:12,595 --> 00:24:13,795
My apologies for being late.

355
00:24:18,905 --> 00:24:20,185
Why are you just standing there?

356
00:24:22,405 --> 00:24:23,925
Go on and do what you came here to do.

357
00:24:25,345 --> 00:24:28,545
It seemed you were all just
waiting for a chance to turn on me.

358
00:24:33,515 --> 00:24:34,915
So why the silence?

359
00:24:35,555 --> 00:24:37,115
- Madam Chair...
- Fine.

360
00:24:38,285 --> 00:24:39,685
Allow me to start.

361
00:24:40,755 --> 00:24:42,625
I understand your intentions perfectly,

362
00:24:43,055 --> 00:24:45,325
and I will process them all immediately.

363
00:24:49,235 --> 00:24:50,235
(Letter of resignation)

364
00:24:57,175 --> 00:24:58,575
Thank you, Attorney Kwon.

365
00:24:58,975 --> 00:25:01,645
I've been meaning to separate
the wheat from the chaff,

366
00:25:01,775 --> 00:25:04,845
and you've just picked
out all the chaff for me.

367
00:25:06,145 --> 00:25:08,955
It seems you're all under
a serious misapprehension.

368
00:25:10,015 --> 00:25:12,555
You are not the ones who
built Haeil into what it is today.

369
00:25:13,085 --> 00:25:15,925
Haeil made you who you are today.

370
00:25:18,565 --> 00:25:20,565
Anyone who defies me.

371
00:25:21,325 --> 00:25:22,735
I cut them out.

372
00:25:23,295 --> 00:25:24,695
When it comes to traitors,

373
00:25:25,335 --> 00:25:28,235
I've never failed to remove
them from the industry.

374
00:25:32,075 --> 00:25:34,945
Please forgive me, ma'am. I was foolish.

375
00:25:36,345 --> 00:25:37,375
I was wrong.

376
00:25:39,415 --> 00:25:41,055
- Please forgive me.
- Please forgive me.

377
00:25:53,625 --> 00:25:55,035
Back when we were young,

378
00:25:55,495 --> 00:25:58,195
you used to say you were sick
of only attending law lectures,

379
00:25:58,765 --> 00:26:01,605
so we used to sneak into
classes in other departments.

380
00:26:02,875 --> 00:26:03,975
Remember that?

381
00:26:04,535 --> 00:26:05,545
Yes.

382
00:26:06,975 --> 00:26:10,675
Wasn't it an Intro to
Literature class we sat in on?

383
00:26:13,015 --> 00:26:17,485
I really disliked King
Lear, Hamlet, and Macbeth.

384
00:26:20,325 --> 00:26:23,795
The kings all lose their
thrones. So foolishly.

385
00:26:29,995 --> 00:26:31,065
Jung Hyeon.

386
00:26:31,635 --> 00:26:33,981
When a child is acting up,
you're supposed to correct them.

387
00:26:34,005 --> 00:26:35,805
Not play along with them.

388
00:26:42,545 --> 00:26:43,745
I have no excuse.

389
00:26:45,515 --> 00:26:46,515
That's right.

390
00:26:47,985 --> 00:26:50,055
You shouldn't have one.

391
00:26:51,255 --> 00:26:52,485
I knew it.

392
00:26:53,355 --> 00:26:55,025
The reason Park Je Yeol showed up.

393
00:26:57,155 --> 00:27:00,525
He's using our past to stop
us from pursuing Connect.

394
00:27:02,835 --> 00:27:04,395
But what if Park Je Yeol

395
00:27:05,105 --> 00:27:06,305
really goes public with it?

396
00:27:07,965 --> 00:27:09,775
Hyun Jin would be in the most danger.

397
00:27:12,305 --> 00:27:14,975
But we can't just surrender.

398
00:27:15,715 --> 00:27:17,115
Especially not to that jerk.

399
00:27:17,515 --> 00:27:20,715
- Worst-case scenario, you could...
- Get arrested?

400
00:27:22,755 --> 00:27:26,325
You think the lawyers here would
just stand by and let that happen?

401
00:27:27,725 --> 00:27:30,195
And we would probably

402
00:27:31,055 --> 00:27:32,595
lose everything.

403
00:27:34,365 --> 00:27:36,005
Everything we've worked so hard to build.

404
00:27:39,435 --> 00:27:41,665
But if we're prepared to
fight this to the very end,

405
00:27:41,735 --> 00:27:44,235
your opinion is what matters
most to Hyun Jin and me.

406
00:27:44,735 --> 00:27:47,405
Can you handle what's coming?

407
00:27:53,015 --> 00:27:56,055
About that DNA sample from
before, the one Seon Kyu took.

408
00:27:56,355 --> 00:27:57,885
It ended up in Park Je Yeol's hands.

409
00:27:58,855 --> 00:28:02,095
- What are you talking about?
- So, does that ring any bells?

410
00:28:03,455 --> 00:28:06,295
But do you even know who my husband is?

411
00:28:06,765 --> 00:28:08,065
He's a sitting prosecutor.

412
00:28:25,115 --> 00:28:26,115
Ju Hwan.

413
00:28:27,115 --> 00:28:28,115
Park Ju Hwan.

414
00:28:30,685 --> 00:28:32,525
Ju Hwan, I've been
looking all over for you.

415
00:28:32,785 --> 00:28:35,025
I told you not to smile at other guys.

416
00:28:35,955 --> 00:28:39,095
I'm sorry. Let's go. Everyone's waiting.

417
00:28:40,225 --> 00:28:41,725
You don't love me at all.

418
00:28:42,965 --> 00:28:44,235
You just say you do.

419
00:28:45,265 --> 00:28:46,805
Then what do you want me to do?

420
00:28:47,065 --> 00:28:48,825
What do I have to do
to make you believe me?

421
00:28:49,535 --> 00:28:50,605
Prove it.

422
00:28:51,435 --> 00:28:52,505
Are you crazy?

423
00:28:55,215 --> 00:28:56,815
Let go. Don't!

424
00:29:01,215 --> 00:29:02,215
No!

425
00:29:35,815 --> 00:29:38,855
Why give me the cold shoulder
just because you got a few wrong?

426
00:29:39,425 --> 00:29:41,585
Because I changed my
scantron answer and got it wrong!

427
00:29:41,995 --> 00:29:43,095
This is so frustrating.

428
00:29:43,795 --> 00:29:45,795
If you keep that up,
you're going to regret it.

429
00:29:46,495 --> 00:29:47,495
Here.

430
00:29:48,965 --> 00:29:50,165
(Super concert!)

431
00:29:51,365 --> 00:29:54,035
No way! Dad, how did you get these?

432
00:29:54,405 --> 00:29:56,175
What do you mean? I bought them, of course.

433
00:29:56,475 --> 00:29:59,375
I'm practically an expert
at nabbing tickets now.

434
00:30:00,075 --> 00:30:01,275
Thanks, Dad.

435
00:30:07,445 --> 00:30:10,885
- Dad, come on. Mom's waiting.
- Right, let's go in.

436
00:30:41,785 --> 00:30:42,855
(Family Registry)

437
00:30:42,915 --> 00:30:45,195
(Hong Yeon Hui, Spouse:
Park Je Yeol, Child: Park Sang A)

438
00:30:54,465 --> 00:30:57,095
- Having indigestion?
- No, it's my lower abdomen.

439
00:30:59,535 --> 00:31:02,105
Are you sure it's not cramps?
Want some painkillers?

440
00:31:12,515 --> 00:31:13,545
What's this?

441
00:31:16,815 --> 00:31:18,055
What do you think you're doing?

442
00:31:20,185 --> 00:31:21,425
Well...

443
00:31:22,755 --> 00:31:25,525
- Orders came from above...
- What orders?

444
00:31:33,265 --> 00:31:34,835
(Managing Partner Kang Shin Jae)

445
00:31:36,935 --> 00:31:39,475
I'm Kwon Jung Hyeon, the new head of LnJ.

446
00:31:40,175 --> 00:31:41,735
I look forward to working with you all.

447
00:31:42,345 --> 00:31:43,705
(Managing Partner Kwon Jung Hyeon)

448
00:31:46,585 --> 00:31:48,115
What do you think you're doing?

449
00:31:48,485 --> 00:31:51,115
Consider this my response to your message.

450
00:31:51,815 --> 00:31:53,925
You shouldn't have one.

451
00:31:54,525 --> 00:31:58,225
- I trust you're ready to pay.
- About Shin Jae.

452
00:32:00,725 --> 00:32:02,685
I will take responsibility
and send her to Haeil.

453
00:32:04,595 --> 00:32:06,305
I'll resign from all my positions.

454
00:32:06,805 --> 00:32:08,265
Just send me to LnJ.

455
00:32:11,005 --> 00:32:12,965
You have to be able to
weather a storm like this.

456
00:32:14,205 --> 00:32:15,915
Drop all your current cases.

457
00:32:16,415 --> 00:32:21,085
I'm changing the firm's direction.
Women aren't the only vulnerable.

458
00:32:22,985 --> 00:32:24,885
You can't just do this out of the blue.

459
00:32:25,215 --> 00:32:26,401
We've been using our
own free time to take

460
00:32:26,425 --> 00:32:29,655
a ton of pro bono cases. If
you make us drop them all

461
00:32:29,725 --> 00:32:31,955
I also saw some cases
that were getting bad press.

462
00:32:32,925 --> 00:32:36,495
Why should your volunteer
work tarnish the firm's name?

463
00:32:38,435 --> 00:32:41,965
Who do you all think signs your paychecks?

464
00:32:42,505 --> 00:32:45,475
From now on, no cases or
assignments without my approval.

465
00:32:46,045 --> 00:32:47,805
When the steering
committee meets next year,

466
00:32:48,205 --> 00:32:50,685
I don't want to be torn apart
for being an incompetent leader.

467
00:32:51,475 --> 00:32:52,845
Like you were, Shin Jae.

468
00:32:53,385 --> 00:32:55,345
This is all because of Connect, isn't it?

469
00:32:55,755 --> 00:32:57,995
You're trying to stop us from
exposing what Connect did.

470
00:32:58,115 --> 00:33:00,325
- Am I wrong?
- Well

471
00:33:00,655 --> 00:33:03,995
I don't know what you
mean, but what I do know is

472
00:33:04,155 --> 00:33:07,925
that the Jo Yoo Jeong case
is closed due to her suicide.

473
00:33:08,425 --> 00:33:12,735
This is no playground to waste
time writing some ridiculous fantasy.

474
00:33:24,545 --> 00:33:26,345
The person you are
calling is unavailable...

475
00:33:26,445 --> 00:33:28,315
(Mom)

476
00:33:31,855 --> 00:33:34,255
(Lee Seon Hwa)

477
00:33:36,495 --> 00:33:38,195
I know everything you did to me.

478
00:33:38,725 --> 00:33:39,765
Call me.

479
00:35:05,045 --> 00:35:07,045
You've been giving me
a lot to worry about lately.

480
00:35:08,645 --> 00:35:09,655
Mark my words.

481
00:35:10,085 --> 00:35:12,425
If you keep acting up, Yoon
Ra Young is going to get hurt.

482
00:36:22,795 --> 00:36:23,795
Min Seo.

483
00:36:47,015 --> 00:36:48,315
I'm at the hotel.

484
00:36:49,085 --> 00:36:50,085
Where are you?

485
00:36:50,755 --> 00:36:54,125
In the government's national
pilot smart city project,

486
00:36:54,325 --> 00:36:56,995
The Prime is being mentioned
as the most promising candidate.

487
00:36:57,755 --> 00:37:00,401
That predictive defence
system you mentioned

488
00:37:00,425 --> 00:37:01,601
- would ultimately...
- You're here.

489
00:37:01,625 --> 00:37:03,165
We need to talk.

490
00:37:03,235 --> 00:37:06,205
We need to talk about Attorney Kwon.
How could you, without telling me?

491
00:37:06,235 --> 00:37:07,275
That would be unavoidable.

492
00:37:07,305 --> 00:37:09,105
You also went behind my back,

493
00:37:09,275 --> 00:37:10,981
scheming something interesting of your own.

494
00:37:11,005 --> 00:37:12,421
That concern was our starting point.

495
00:37:12,445 --> 00:37:16,215
Technology shouldn't surveil
people. It should protect them.

496
00:37:16,445 --> 00:37:19,245
Our system doesn't track who is dangerous.

497
00:37:19,385 --> 00:37:22,385
It simply determines which
situations are dangerous.

498
00:37:22,855 --> 00:37:26,785
All data from the smart city project
will be encrypted using block chain.

499
00:37:26,985 --> 00:37:29,855
No identifiable personal
information will be stored,

500
00:37:30,325 --> 00:37:34,795
and it's designed so that no
admin can access the source data.

501
00:37:35,625 --> 00:37:37,535
Why are the reporters taking our picture?

502
00:37:38,035 --> 00:37:40,241
- Didn't you see the news?
- What news?

503
00:37:40,265 --> 00:37:42,835
Redesigning the relationship...

504
00:37:43,505 --> 00:37:46,545
Corruption by the powerful, a
system free from human prejudice...

505
00:37:46,605 --> 00:37:48,105
You were outmanoeuvred.

506
00:37:48,445 --> 00:37:50,451
("Prime CEO Baek Tae Joo
Engaged to Haeil's Successor?")

507
00:37:50,475 --> 00:37:51,791
For even the most vulnerable...

508
00:37:51,815 --> 00:37:53,285
Was this your doing?

509
00:37:53,385 --> 00:37:55,885
I've let you off the leash for too long.

510
00:37:56,255 --> 00:37:58,291
- So I've learned my lesson.
- Our technology will be the tool...

511
00:37:58,315 --> 00:37:59,325
And him?

512
00:37:59,385 --> 00:38:01,385
Is he okay with articles like this?

513
00:38:01,585 --> 00:38:05,025
That is the one and only goal
The Prime aims to achieve.

514
00:38:05,095 --> 00:38:06,975
(The Prime: Technology,
Setting a New Standard)

515
00:38:08,595 --> 00:38:11,035
Quiet. People are watching.

516
00:38:13,135 --> 00:38:16,475
Excuse me, sir, but a report about
your engagement just came out.

517
00:38:16,775 --> 00:38:18,305
Is there any truth to the article?

518
00:38:19,645 --> 00:38:20,845
The engagement rumour

519
00:38:21,975 --> 00:38:23,075
is not true.

520
00:38:25,475 --> 00:38:28,585
However, it is true that
I have feelings for her.

521
00:38:29,755 --> 00:38:31,635
(The Prime: Technology,
Setting a New Standard)

522
00:38:45,065 --> 00:38:46,335
Pardon the intrusion.

523
00:38:46,735 --> 00:38:48,895
This is the only place we
can talk without being seen.

524
00:38:49,775 --> 00:38:51,015
What do you think you're doing?

525
00:38:51,305 --> 00:38:52,375
What do you mean?

526
00:38:52,975 --> 00:38:57,175
Why are you siding with my
mother? And making things up, no less.

527
00:38:57,245 --> 00:38:58,475
I wasn't lying.

528
00:38:59,885 --> 00:39:02,285
I corrected the engagement rumour,

529
00:39:03,055 --> 00:39:05,515
and as for my feelings
for you, Attorney Kang...

530
00:39:06,525 --> 00:39:07,555
That part is true.

531
00:39:09,755 --> 00:39:13,065
Do you realise we've only
met a handful of times?

532
00:39:13,195 --> 00:39:14,365
Even before we ever met.

533
00:39:14,825 --> 00:39:16,625
I've been interested
from the very beginning.

534
00:39:17,695 --> 00:39:19,535
What deal did you make with my mother?

535
00:39:19,835 --> 00:39:21,535
Or what do you want from me?

536
00:39:23,375 --> 00:39:25,375
Is that always how you approach people?

537
00:39:25,675 --> 00:39:27,505
As a transaction, not a relationship.

538
00:39:27,675 --> 00:39:29,245
Profit over trust.

539
00:39:29,675 --> 00:39:30,845
And what's wrong with that?

540
00:39:31,515 --> 00:39:35,015
I happen to think we could be a great team.

541
00:39:35,315 --> 00:39:37,561
- And not as business partners.
- What's that supposed to mean?

542
00:39:37,585 --> 00:39:39,061
Try a different perspective.

543
00:39:39,085 --> 00:39:40,725
I'm not an enemy siding with your mother.

544
00:39:41,025 --> 00:39:44,255
I could be an ally who
empowers you, Attorney Kang.

545
00:39:44,625 --> 00:39:46,695
Why would you choose me over my mother?

546
00:39:48,565 --> 00:39:50,265
Because the one I find impressive

547
00:39:51,365 --> 00:39:52,565
is you, Attorney Kang.

548
00:39:53,165 --> 00:39:54,335
Not CEO Seong.

549
00:39:57,735 --> 00:39:58,835
Oh, right.

550
00:39:59,875 --> 00:40:02,505
I won't bother issuing a retraction
for that engagement story.

551
00:40:03,075 --> 00:40:04,675
You never know, it might just come true.

552
00:40:09,015 --> 00:40:10,015
See you around.

553
00:40:27,765 --> 00:40:28,765
Here. Drink this.

554
00:40:42,415 --> 00:40:46,025
I was so hungry, so I
stole my neighbour's milk.

555
00:40:48,555 --> 00:40:49,555
When I was six.

556
00:40:50,595 --> 00:40:51,925
I hadn't eaten in three days.

557
00:40:54,625 --> 00:40:57,025
As punishment, I was locked
out on the balcony for two days.

558
00:40:59,165 --> 00:41:00,235
In just my underwear.

559
00:41:03,675 --> 00:41:04,875
And it was January.

560
00:41:07,105 --> 00:41:08,385
When I was in elementary school,

561
00:41:09,315 --> 00:41:11,915
I ran an errand and messed up the change.

562
00:41:14,115 --> 00:41:17,055
And my entire body
became black with bruises.

563
00:41:18,255 --> 00:41:19,985
My parents were always like that.

564
00:41:20,885 --> 00:41:22,995
They said if you do something
bad, you get punished.

565
00:41:24,725 --> 00:41:26,495
Is it because I'm a bad person

566
00:41:28,465 --> 00:41:30,265
that this is happening to me?

567
00:41:36,275 --> 00:41:37,275
Min Seo.

568
00:41:38,675 --> 00:41:42,075
Could you ever stab someone with a knife?

569
00:41:45,115 --> 00:41:46,115
You couldn't, could you?

570
00:41:47,085 --> 00:41:49,285
Then why would you do that to yourself?

571
00:41:53,355 --> 00:41:54,635
I used to do that to myself too.

572
00:41:55,455 --> 00:41:59,365
"Why did I go there? Why
couldn't I see who he truly was?"

573
00:42:00,765 --> 00:42:05,035
"Something this awful happened to
me because I was naive and stupid."

574
00:42:05,535 --> 00:42:08,305
The kind of cruel blame I
would never put on anyone else,

575
00:42:09,035 --> 00:42:11,605
I'd turn it on myself hundreds,
even thousands of times.

576
00:42:14,745 --> 00:42:16,045
And do you know why?

577
00:42:18,675 --> 00:42:20,945
Because I was my own easiest target.

578
00:42:23,115 --> 00:42:25,475
I should've been mad at my
tormentor, at this unjust world.

579
00:42:26,255 --> 00:42:28,625
But I didn't have the
courage to fight back,

580
00:42:29,225 --> 00:42:30,425
so I was just taking it out

581
00:42:31,455 --> 00:42:32,695
on someone weak.

582
00:42:33,365 --> 00:42:34,925
Myself, the easiest person,

583
00:42:36,235 --> 00:42:37,235
for me to hurt.

584
00:42:39,565 --> 00:42:40,605
Blaming yourself

585
00:42:41,835 --> 00:42:44,075
is the most convenient way

586
00:42:45,005 --> 00:42:46,775
to be a coward. That's what I realised.

587
00:42:51,545 --> 00:42:52,545
I

588
00:42:53,745 --> 00:42:57,455
Want you to break up
with yesterday, Min Seo.

589
00:42:58,155 --> 00:43:01,225
And I want you to start
showing some respect

590
00:43:01,785 --> 00:43:03,095
to yourself.

591
00:43:08,295 --> 00:43:09,995
Someone from Connect came to see me.

592
00:43:11,095 --> 00:43:15,205
They said if I keep helping LnJ,
they're going to come after you.

593
00:43:16,075 --> 00:43:18,635
- From now on, you must never...
- When things like this happen,

594
00:43:19,105 --> 00:43:20,445
it feels like confirmation

595
00:43:20,975 --> 00:43:21,975
of who I really am.

596
00:43:23,115 --> 00:43:25,815
That I can never be
normal like everyone else.

597
00:43:26,385 --> 00:43:29,385
And that I'll never be able to escape it.

598
00:43:32,415 --> 00:43:34,585
I don't want much. I just

599
00:43:36,295 --> 00:43:38,255
want to get back the things I've lost.

600
00:43:40,495 --> 00:43:41,765
Can I get it all back?

601
00:43:42,935 --> 00:43:44,495
Even after I've ruined everything?

602
00:43:56,545 --> 00:43:57,545
You're up?

603
00:43:58,845 --> 00:44:01,045
I figured a proper meal
would be better for breakfast.

604
00:44:01,385 --> 00:44:02,745
How are you feeling? Are you okay?

605
00:44:03,755 --> 00:44:04,785
Yes.

606
00:44:06,185 --> 00:44:07,785
Did you make all this just for me?

607
00:44:08,255 --> 00:44:09,655
You said you don't eat breakfast.

608
00:44:10,955 --> 00:44:11,955
Have a seat.

609
00:44:23,075 --> 00:44:25,305
A while back, when I
was having a hard time,

610
00:44:26,605 --> 00:44:31,245
I couldn't eat anything for a while.
I couldn't get a single bite down.

611
00:44:32,615 --> 00:44:36,555
While I wasn't eating, my
friends refused to eat too.

612
00:44:37,285 --> 00:44:39,725
For them, I forced down
one bite, then another.

613
00:44:40,425 --> 00:44:42,855
And slowly, I started to get up,

614
00:44:43,695 --> 00:44:45,625
to walk, and even go outside again.

615
00:44:48,265 --> 00:44:49,465
That's when I realised.

616
00:44:49,835 --> 00:44:51,315
Surviving isn't all that complicated.

617
00:44:51,765 --> 00:44:53,165
I felt like I was going to die,

618
00:44:53,435 --> 00:44:55,435
but once I ate, I found
myself able to live again.

619
00:44:56,065 --> 00:44:58,975
To live, you have to eat.
And to save someone,

620
00:44:59,405 --> 00:45:00,545
you have to feed them.

621
00:45:06,145 --> 00:45:07,515
I'm not going to lie to you.

622
00:45:08,645 --> 00:45:09,655
In the end,

623
00:45:10,285 --> 00:45:12,385
I never fully recovered.

624
00:45:13,755 --> 00:45:17,925
Some wounds heal
without a trace, but others

625
00:45:19,225 --> 00:45:20,995
leave scars that last forever.

626
00:45:23,165 --> 00:45:25,065
Mine was one of those.

627
00:45:26,865 --> 00:45:28,405
But maybe that's

628
00:45:29,505 --> 00:45:33,745
because I never got an apology
from the person who hurt me.

629
00:45:36,845 --> 00:45:38,975
"I'm sorry. I was wrong."

630
00:45:39,345 --> 00:45:40,545
If I get an apology like that,

631
00:45:41,485 --> 00:45:43,855
do you think I might be
a little more okay then?

632
00:45:46,325 --> 00:45:49,325
To find that out, we first need to

633
00:45:49,755 --> 00:45:50,995
eat and get our strength back.

634
00:45:59,535 --> 00:46:00,935
This is from my emergency stash.

635
00:46:01,705 --> 00:46:03,311
It's delicious. It has a nice nutty flavour.

636
00:46:03,335 --> 00:46:04,335
Try some.

637
00:46:18,355 --> 00:46:22,285
Also, Attorney Kwon Jung
Hyeon will be joining LnJ.

638
00:46:23,195 --> 00:46:24,695
The VIP?

639
00:46:25,125 --> 00:46:26,125
Yes.

640
00:46:26,595 --> 00:46:29,895
It's best not to come to the
office for a while, Min Seo.

641
00:46:29,995 --> 00:46:31,355
So you don't have to run into him.

642
00:46:39,235 --> 00:46:40,305
Have you been busy?

643
00:46:41,345 --> 00:46:42,825
I feel like I barely see you anymore.

644
00:46:45,715 --> 00:46:46,985
I just got a new case.

645
00:46:47,745 --> 00:46:48,745
What kind of case?

646
00:46:49,045 --> 00:46:50,491
Attempted murder of a
Hankuk University Law student

647
00:46:50,515 --> 00:46:51,555
from 20 years ago.

648
00:46:54,685 --> 00:46:55,685
What?

649
00:46:55,985 --> 00:46:57,185
The victim's a prosecutor now.

650
00:46:57,425 --> 00:46:59,725
You know him, right?
You two were classmates.

651
00:46:59,965 --> 00:47:03,035
Park Ju Hwan. No, I mean,
Prosecutor Park Je Yeol.

652
00:47:05,165 --> 00:47:08,305
You were ordered to reinvestigate? By who?

653
00:47:08,905 --> 00:47:10,635
By Prosecutor Park Je Yeol himself.

654
00:47:14,175 --> 00:47:17,945
Sorry, I have to head out first.
Can you clean up after me?

655
00:47:42,735 --> 00:47:45,875
(Prosecutor Park Je Yeol)

656
00:47:50,175 --> 00:47:51,475
Yes, Park Je Yeol speaking.

657
00:47:52,215 --> 00:47:54,345
So this is how you're going to pressure us?

658
00:47:54,945 --> 00:47:56,505
How dare you drag my husband into this?

659
00:47:57,955 --> 00:47:59,455
"Drag him?"

660
00:47:59,825 --> 00:48:01,785
I'm just trying to help him score a win.

661
00:48:02,525 --> 00:48:04,245
Besides, I thought it would be interesting.

662
00:48:04,795 --> 00:48:07,165
To have your own husband
be the one to arrest you.

663
00:48:07,425 --> 00:48:10,995
Are you trying to pick
a dirty fight? Is that it?

664
00:48:11,195 --> 00:48:14,935
Detective Gu Seon Kyu seems
like a dedicated, by-the-book guy.

665
00:48:15,735 --> 00:48:18,705
When he learns his wife is a
suspect in an attempted murder case,

666
00:48:19,305 --> 00:48:22,175
I wonder how he'll
react. Aren't you curious?

667
00:48:25,045 --> 00:48:26,415
You stay right where you are.

668
00:48:26,745 --> 00:48:27,785
Yes, come on in.

669
00:48:29,855 --> 00:48:32,295
I'm Detective Gu Seon Kyu
from the Mujin Violent Crimes Unit.

670
00:48:32,855 --> 00:48:35,285
What to do? I seem to
have a prior engagement.

671
00:48:36,255 --> 00:48:37,595
Just use your imagination.

672
00:48:37,925 --> 00:48:39,405
The conversation we're about to have.

673
00:48:42,495 --> 00:48:45,035
Please have a seat.
I've been expecting you.

674
00:49:01,015 --> 00:49:02,775
Have you had a chance
to look into the case?

675
00:49:03,585 --> 00:49:04,585
I have,

676
00:49:04,855 --> 00:49:06,561
but the first investigation was botched,

677
00:49:06,585 --> 00:49:08,325
so there are hardly any leads.

678
00:49:09,285 --> 00:49:10,805
Are you reopening the investigation

679
00:49:11,225 --> 00:49:12,995
because you've regained your memory?

680
00:49:13,395 --> 00:49:15,695
Like you recalled a clue
to the culprit or something.

681
00:49:16,995 --> 00:49:20,505
To be honest, I haven't
fully recovered my memory.

682
00:49:21,205 --> 00:49:22,645
The fragments of memory I do have

683
00:49:22,935 --> 00:49:25,435
I doubt they would even hold up in court.

684
00:49:27,745 --> 00:49:28,745
Then why?

685
00:49:29,205 --> 00:49:32,275
Let's just say I have a hunch.

686
00:49:32,875 --> 00:49:34,115
That you, Detective Gu,

687
00:49:34,415 --> 00:49:36,385
might be the one who can find the culprit.

688
00:49:40,485 --> 00:49:42,325
Is it because I'm Hyun Jin's husband?

689
00:49:46,395 --> 00:49:49,795
So you already knew
about my past with Hyun Jin.

690
00:49:50,835 --> 00:49:52,535
You could say that.

691
00:49:53,605 --> 00:49:57,375
Because you, Detective Gu,

692
00:49:57,675 --> 00:50:00,045
are in a much better
position to get statements

693
00:50:00,405 --> 00:50:02,451
from Yoon Ra Young, Hwang
Hyun Jin, and Kang Shin Jae.

694
00:50:02,475 --> 00:50:04,515
And their memories
should still be perfectly clear.

695
00:50:05,215 --> 00:50:06,215
Really?

696
00:50:07,085 --> 00:50:08,165
Is that all there is to it?

697
00:50:09,985 --> 00:50:10,985
Why do you ask?

698
00:50:11,555 --> 00:50:14,325
Do you have some reason
to suspect there's more to it?

699
00:50:16,425 --> 00:50:18,895
I don't know if this will help,

700
00:50:19,455 --> 00:50:21,725
but Yoon Ra Young and
I were dating at the time.

701
00:50:22,395 --> 00:50:26,635
And on the day of the incident,
all three were there with me.

702
00:50:27,365 --> 00:50:29,835
But the reason they were
never considered suspects

703
00:50:30,205 --> 00:50:32,975
was because they
provided alibis for each other.

704
00:50:34,805 --> 00:50:36,745
Sometimes, I let my imagination run wild.

705
00:50:39,075 --> 00:50:41,785
Were their testimonies actually true?

706
00:50:43,985 --> 00:50:46,161
Then what happened
with Ra Young after that?

707
00:50:46,185 --> 00:50:47,485
We broke up.

708
00:50:48,225 --> 00:50:50,695
More accurately, she's the
one who broke up with me.

709
00:50:52,355 --> 00:50:53,665
Aren't you curious why?

710
00:50:55,365 --> 00:50:57,995
Every now and then, I
find myself wondering.

711
00:51:57,655 --> 00:52:00,595
So you're really going to do
what your mom says again?

712
00:52:01,165 --> 00:52:03,365
I'm thinking about what the best move is.

713
00:52:07,535 --> 00:52:08,535
I'm

714
00:52:09,105 --> 00:52:10,335
done running away.

715
00:52:12,575 --> 00:52:14,405
Hiding it just makes it fester.

716
00:52:15,145 --> 00:52:18,315
Just when I think it's healed,
it always splits open again.

717
00:52:19,545 --> 00:52:23,015
If telling the world is the
price I pay to keep fighting,

718
00:52:24,155 --> 00:52:25,715
I'm willing to pay it, Shin Jae.

719
00:52:28,425 --> 00:52:29,655
Are you sure you'll be okay?

720
00:52:33,195 --> 00:52:34,395
For once,

721
00:52:35,225 --> 00:52:36,895
we should have fought for ourselves.

722
00:52:38,065 --> 00:52:39,065
Connect.

723
00:52:40,105 --> 00:52:41,745
I'm going to see this through to the end.

724
00:52:41,935 --> 00:52:42,935
I can't stop now.

725
00:52:56,385 --> 00:52:57,385
What's wrong?

726
00:53:21,745 --> 00:53:24,175
But the reason they were
never considered suspects

727
00:53:24,475 --> 00:53:27,445
was because they
provided alibis for each other.

728
00:53:29,185 --> 00:53:31,215
Sometimes, I let my imagination run wild.

729
00:53:31,855 --> 00:53:34,255
Were their testimonies actually true?

730
00:53:36,425 --> 00:53:38,825
You know what this reminds me of?

731
00:53:39,525 --> 00:53:40,525
Accomplices.

732
00:53:41,325 --> 00:53:43,295
Their fates are tied together.

733
00:53:44,495 --> 00:53:45,695
If one of them goes down,

734
00:53:46,265 --> 00:53:48,665
the other is bound to go down with them.

735
00:54:02,245 --> 00:54:04,315
I took another one. It's the same.

736
00:54:05,155 --> 00:54:08,055
He doesn't know yet. I haven't told him.

737
00:54:09,155 --> 00:54:10,715
For now, you're the only ones who know.

738
00:54:11,625 --> 00:54:12,625
As for telling him...

739
00:54:12,995 --> 00:54:16,025
Shouldn't I wait until I'm more sure?

740
00:54:18,935 --> 00:54:21,005
- I'm home.
- Hey.

741
00:54:25,505 --> 00:54:26,505
You're back?

742
00:54:29,045 --> 00:54:30,045
What now?

743
00:54:31,815 --> 00:54:32,815
What?

744
00:54:33,485 --> 00:54:35,045
Something else you're hiding from me.

745
00:54:35,545 --> 00:54:36,645
What on earth is it now?

746
00:54:38,455 --> 00:54:40,425
What are you talking about all of a sudden?

747
00:54:41,525 --> 00:54:43,005
What are you hiding behind your back?

748
00:54:43,355 --> 00:54:44,455
What am I hiding?

749
00:54:55,605 --> 00:54:58,005
No. We can't. Things have changed.

750
00:54:58,535 --> 00:55:00,405
You know how long Hyun
Jin has wanted a baby.

751
00:55:00,875 --> 00:55:02,405
If what we did gets out,

752
00:55:02,775 --> 00:55:04,315
Hyun Jin will be in the most danger.

753
00:55:04,575 --> 00:55:06,615
Protecting Hyun Jin has to come first.

754
00:55:08,185 --> 00:55:11,415
You're right. It's too reckless
to just charge ahead like this.

755
00:55:19,995 --> 00:55:21,475
Here's the information you asked for.

756
00:55:22,065 --> 00:55:23,065
Thank you.

757
00:55:25,095 --> 00:55:27,035
Is this for real?

758
00:55:31,405 --> 00:55:34,445
I was going to tell you
once I was more certain.

759
00:55:35,845 --> 00:55:38,285
I was afraid you'd be disappointed
if something went wrong...

760
00:55:39,375 --> 00:55:41,845
How can you say that?

761
00:55:45,215 --> 00:55:46,885
We're going to be parents?

762
00:55:48,585 --> 00:55:49,585
Really?

763
00:55:50,325 --> 00:55:53,595
- Why are you crying, silly?
- I'm not crying.

764
00:55:54,165 --> 00:55:55,165
I'm just so happy.

765
00:56:00,605 --> 00:56:02,105
There might be a way.

766
00:56:04,605 --> 00:56:07,345
Park Je Yeol. We take him down first.

767
00:56:08,175 --> 00:56:09,845
So he can't breathe a word about us.

768
00:56:29,295 --> 00:56:30,765
Hong Yeon Hui, age 42.

769
00:56:31,165 --> 00:56:34,005
Spouse, a prosecutor, Mujin
Prosecutors' Office, Division Three,

770
00:56:34,265 --> 00:56:35,265
Park Je Yeol.

771
00:56:39,605 --> 00:56:40,605
You.

772
00:56:41,745 --> 00:56:43,615
What's your real reason for approaching me?

773
00:56:53,955 --> 00:56:54,955
It was you, wasn't it?

774
00:56:55,325 --> 00:56:57,855
You're the one who tried to
kill my husband 20 years ago.

775
00:57:01,595 --> 00:57:02,665
It was a mistake.

776
00:57:07,765 --> 00:57:09,635
I should have finished him off back then.

777
00:57:28,555 --> 00:57:32,455
(Honour)

778
00:58:23,875 --> 00:58:26,715
Attempted murder of a male student
at Hankuk University College of Law.

779
00:58:26,815 --> 00:58:29,845
If this happens to Hyun Jin
again, I swear I won't let it slide.

780
00:58:30,715 --> 00:58:32,585
You're telling me this
is Jun Hyeok's laptop?

781
00:58:32,855 --> 00:58:34,861
I'll give you an exclusive,
and I'll even do an interview.

782
00:58:34,885 --> 00:58:37,825
Attorney Kwon is involved. As a user.

783
00:58:38,225 --> 00:58:40,665
I said I would help you.
That was our deal, wasn't it?

784
00:58:40,825 --> 00:58:43,565
I've laid all my cards on the
table. So, what do you want?

785
00:58:44,435 --> 00:58:47,335
- Mission complete.
- Jun Hyeok's laptop is gone.

786
00:58:47,765 --> 00:58:49,565
If there's someone who
hasn't paid their due,

787
00:58:49,805 --> 00:58:50,805
It's you.
